THE STRUCTURE OF FORMS

Reference
Element: <form>...</form>
Attributes: {action, method}
Example: <form action="url_to_send_form_data" method="post">...</form>

Element: <input.../>
Attributes: {type, name, maxlength, value}
Example: <input type="text" name="firstname" />

Element: <label>...</label>
Attributes: {for, id}
Example: <label for="first_name">...</label>

Element: <textarea>...</textarea>
Attributes: {id, rows, cols}
Example: <textarea id="message" rows="5" cols="20"></textarea>

Element: <fieldset>...</fieldset>
Attributes: {}
Example: This element is used to delineate sections of a large form.

Element: <select>...</select>
Attributes: {id}
Example: <select id="countries">...</select>

Element: <option>...</option>
Attributes: {value}
Example: The option element is nested within a select element to create a list of choices.

Element: <button>...</button>
Attributes: {type}
Example: <button type="submit">Submit</button>
